phrs.translation: 不能实行的, 难以实施的, 不可行的, 不可能的
这个计划是个架空的东西, 使徒具虚名

sentences.sentence: The weather made it unfeasible to be outdoors.
Opening up new farmland was a possibility, but most of what was suitable had already been exploited and further reclamation was technically unfeasible.
sentences.translation: 开辟新农田是可能的，但大部分适宜的土地已经开发，进一步开垦在技术上是不可行的。

sentences.sentence: Though possible in theory, the cost and effort of doing so makes this unfeasible in practice.
sentences.translation: 虽然这个方法理论上可行，但是其成本和代价使其在实际操作中难以实施。
